<TITLE> HC orders halt to filling Sandhya river </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 31 (bdnews24.com)The High Court has ordered the government to suspend the filling in of a river bank, for a housing development in Barisal, for three months. A two-judge bench of justices Syed Mahmud Hossain and Kamrul Islam Siddiqui also served the a rule nisi on the government as to why filling the banks of the Sandhya river should not be declared illegal and why a order should not be issued to stop the filling permanently. The court has asked the local government secretary, Barisal deputy commissioner, Barisal executive engineer, Banaripara upazila nirbahi officer to answer the rule within four weeks. The rule came following a pubic interest petition filed by Human Rights and Peace for Bangladesh on May 18. Participant in the hearing, advocate Manjil Morshed, said according to environmental and water body laws, creating a housing project by filling in river banks is illegal. But the government did not take any effective measures to stop the filling of the Sandhya river, he said. bdn
